But it is not as scary and difficult as you may think.

02:40.000 --> 02:45.000
Accounting

02:45.000 --> 02:52.000
In general, accounting consists of two simple operations – addition and subtraction.

02:52.000 --> 02:59.000
We will have to understand and believe this in the following examples.

02:59.000 --> 03:04.000
You are managers of different levels.

03:04.000 --> 03:15.000
Management is the ability to make decisions based on information about the economic processes that take place at your enterprise.

03:15.000 --> 03:29.000
Accounting is the process of creating information about the financial situation of the organization to the relevant persons who are interested in its activities.

03:29.000 --> 03:38.000
The process of creating information involves a certain procedure that includes the sequence of the accountant's actions,

03:38.000 --> 03:47.000
as a result of which the data on the facts of the organization's economic activities are converted into accounting elements.

03:47.000 --> 03:53.000
We can build a chain of the accountant's actions.

03:53.000 --> 04:01.000
First, the primary documents are created. Primary documents are not always created by the accountant.

04:01.000 --> 04:05.000
They are created by managers and other enterprises.

04:05.000 --> 04:12.000
The primary documents, their data, are put into accounting registers.

04:12.000 --> 04:21.000
The information from the accounting registers is used to form the accounting report of the organization.

04:21.000 --> 04:24.000
What is it for?

04:24.000 --> 04:30.000
The accounting report has its users.

04:30.000 --> 04:38.000
All users can be divided into two groups – the group of internal users and the group of external users.

04:38.000 --> 04:54.000
The internal users include the management, the financial analysis, accounting information for production or management,

04:54.000 --> 05:04.000
the owners of the organization's property, the personnel of the organization, external users, shareholders,

05:04.000 --> 05:15.000
members of the economic societies interested in the financial result, investors, creditors, potential agents,

05:15.000 --> 05:25.000
partners within the framework of the group of interrelated organizations, and, of course, the controlling fiscal bodies,

05:25.000 --> 05:36.000
tax authorities, law enforcement agencies, the audit firms and the statistical bodies.

05:37.000 --> 05:58.000
To satisfy each user, different methods of data grouping and their detailing are used in accordance with the users' requests.

05:59.000 --> 06:09.000
For example, the accounting balance and the profit and loss report are of the greatest interest to the organization's management.

06:09.000 --> 06:22.000
These main reporting forms contain data for two consecutive periods – the past period and the previous reporting period –

06:22.000 --> 06:30.000
and allow for direct monitoring of the main performance indicators of the enterprise.

06:30.000 --> 06:42.000
All selection is carried out from the same data, the same data is obtained by different users.

06:42.000 --> 06:49.000
These data should be identical, but their grouping methods may be different.

06:49.000 --> 07:03.000
Various approaches to grouping and detailing accounting information are provided by the development and introduction of the main and auxiliary forms of analytical accounting accounting.

07:03.000 --> 07:13.000
Let's talk a little more about the groups of users and their economic interests.

07:14.000 --> 07:30.000
The shareholders, who we call the owners of the enterprise, transfer such resources as the investment in the established capital to the economic turnover.

07:30.000 --> 07:49.000
These investments can be financial or material. In addition, the profit received from the enterprise's activities is also allowed to be invested in the enterprise.

07:49.000 --> 08:07.000
Accordingly, the information on the risk of their decision, the profitability they expect to receive from the investments,

08:07.000 --> 08:17.000
the opportunities and the expediency of the organization's investments, and the ability of the organization to pay dividends.

08:17.000 --> 08:23.000
The next group of users is managers, employees, and the organization's personnel.

08:23.000 --> 08:36.000
What can they invest in the organization? They invest their work, the services they have produced but have not yet paid, or the deposit salary,

08:36.000 --> 08:45.000
the money that remains at the disposal of the enterprise. What information can interest them? Will they get their salary?

08:45.000 --> 08:54.000
What can they invest in the organization? Will they get their salary?

08:54.000 --> 09:10.000
The next group of users is the investors. They invest their money and hope to get some interest from the organization.

09:10.000 --> 09:25.000
They are interested in whether they can temporarily pay the loans they are provided with, whether they will receive the corresponding interest, and whether payments will be made in their favor.

09:25.000 --> 09:39.000
The next group of users is business partners of the organization. They are suppliers, contractors, buyers, customers, and lenders.

09:39.000 --> 09:56.000
This group of users either imports goods by making goods loans, provides advance payments to the organization, or is transferred to the property lending.

09:56.000 --> 10:07.000
They are interested in the information about the payment in advance of the rent, commission payments, and the discount of the sale, and the term of the payment in advance.

10:08.000 --> 10:30.000
Another group of users is the state. They are the tax authorities, the state provides the money,

10:30.000 --> 10:46.000
which is in circulation in the organization, in the amount of the tax obligations, in particular, the single social tax, the deductions to pension funds, and the salaries of workers.

10:46.000 --> 10:55.000
They are interested in how much taxes and fees, duties, excises, and other non-tax payments will be transferred in due time.

10:55.000 --> 11:02.000
They are interested in the information for statistical monitoring.

11:17.000 --> 11:32.000
When can an accounting account be organized? It is known that as soon as we decide what to count, then we can talk about the organization of an accounting account.

11:32.000 --> 11:42.000
Will we count cash and cashless money, debt, equipment, material values, unfinished production, and so on?

11:42.000 --> 11:53.000
We will divide all the objects of accounting study into two large groups. We make two new definitions.

11:54.000 --> 12:02.000
One group is called assets, and we will include all the organization's funds and their movements.

12:02.000 --> 12:11.000
The other group is called passives, and we will include the sources of education and use of the organization's funds.

12:11.000 --> 12:29.000
The organization's funds can also be divided into groups such as the main assets, non-material assets, and call them non-return funds.

12:29.000 --> 12:41.000
The main assets are the buildings and structures that are built, and the non-return funds are the funds that are not used.

12:41.000 --> 12:47.000
Let's see in more detail what will be included in these groups.

12:47.000 --> 12:53.000
The non-return funds, as I said, are divided into the main assets and non-material assets.

12:53.000 --> 13:01.000
The main assets include the buildings and structures that belong to the organization,

13:01.000 --> 13:14.000
the work and power equipment, measuring and regulating devices, computing equipment, transport, tools, household inventory, and road infrastructure.

13:14.000 --> 13:24.000
Non-material assets are those that do not have a material form, but also belong to the organization.

13:24.000 --> 13:30.000
These are patents for inventions, trademarks, and the concept of Goodwill.

13:30.000 --> 13:36.000
We will discuss this concept in more detail a little later.

13:36.000 --> 13:49.000
The next group of non-return funds is the call funds.

13:49.000 --> 13:58.000
The non-return funds include production reserves, unfinished production, and future periods.

13:58.000 --> 14:13.000
We will define this as a name, and later we will give a more detailed explanation to these non-return funds.

14:13.000 --> 14:25.000
The production reserves are materials, semi-finished products, and blanks for production and trading enterprises.

14:25.000 --> 14:36.000
The call funds are used to account for ready-made products of production enterprises,

14:36.000 --> 14:47.000
the funds in the accounts for the positions of your customers, that is, the product that you have already released but have not yet been paid for,

14:47.000 --> 14:58.000
the money that is in the cash register and on the accounts of the organization, short-term financial investments of the organization, and other turnover assets.

14:58.000 --> 15:07.000
Another group of funds is the withdrawn funds, which are temporarily or irrevocably withdrawn from the economic turnover.

15:07.000 --> 15:17.000
The paid funds are irrevocably withdrawn from the budget, and the temporarily withdrawn funds are reimbursed taxes.

15:17.000 --> 15:21.000
There is a tax on the added value of the acquired assets.

15:21.000 --> 15:36.000
You buy the materials and pay the tax on the added value, and then you have the right to pay this tax after the acquisition of the assets.

15:36.000 --> 15:46.000
The payments for the use of the bank's loans will also be counted in the withdrawn funds of the organization.

15:47.000 --> 15:56.000
We have already discussed the assets of the organization.

15:56.000 --> 16:11.000
Let me remind you that these are the main funds, non-material assets, long-term financial investments, unfinished construction, and income investments in material values.

16:11.000 --> 16:15.000
All of these will be called non-returnable assets.

16:15.000 --> 16:28.000
The non-returnable assets include stocks, raw materials, ready-made products, unfinished production, and short-term financial investments.

16:28.000 --> 16:34.000
I would like to draw your attention to the fact that long-term financial investments are included in the group of non-returnable assets,

16:34.000 --> 16:43.000
and short-term financial investments, which the enterprise invests in a group of returnable assets for up to 12 months,

16:43.000 --> 16:48.000
also include money and debtors' debts.

16:48.000 --> 16:56.000
Another group of withdrawn assets is the payment to the budget, reimbursable taxes, and payments for the use of the bank's loans.

16:56.000 --> 17:01.000
We have already discussed the concept of the asset of the organization.

17:01.000 --> 17:21.000
The second part of the balance sheet will consist of passives or sources, which are used to purchase the organization's assets.

17:21.000 --> 17:26.000
The passives can also be divided into three parts.

17:26.000 --> 17:40.000
The passives are the organization's own funds, the loan funds, and a group of additional funds that will participate in the organization's money circulation.

17:40.000 --> 17:49.000
The original, own funds that any organization receives when it registers are its fixed capital.

17:49.000 --> 17:55.000
As the organization works, additional capital is formed.

17:55.000 --> 18:02.000
The organization has the right to create various reserve funds, and gradually reserve capital is formed.

18:02.000 --> 18:12.000
The organization earns profits. All commercial organizations in Russia are created to make profits.

18:12.000 --> 18:22.000
This unallocated profit is also formed by the organization's own funds.

18:22.000 --> 18:31.000
The loan funds consist of loans and loans, long-term loans, which are received for more than 12 months,

18:31.000 --> 18:39.000
and short-term loans and loans, which must be returned within a year.

18:40.000 --> 18:48.000
Additional funds are salary contributions, which are temporarily in the company's use,

18:48.000 --> 18:54.000
the budget for taxes and fees, social insurance contributions,

18:54.000 --> 18:58.000
and contributions to suppliers and other creditors.

18:58.000 --> 19:03.000
And the reserve of the upcoming expenses.

19:04.000 --> 19:13.000
We have divided the organization's assets into assets and passives.

19:13.000 --> 19:20.000
Now we have to decide what to measure.

19:20.000 --> 19:28.000
We have to measure the machines that the organization owns,

19:28.000 --> 19:37.000
and measure the collective's labor investments, and calculate the organization's capital.

19:37.000 --> 19:42.000
There must be a single, universal unit.

19:43.000 --> 19:51.000
The measurers you know can be divided into natural, labor, and monetary.

19:51.000 --> 19:54.000
Natural ones are used to determine the object.

19:54.000 --> 19:58.000
We can count objects in pieces, in kilograms, in meters.

19:58.000 --> 20:04.000
We need labor measurers to determine the amount of labor spent.

20:04.000 --> 20:07.000
Whether it is a working day, an hour.

20:07.000 --> 20:15.000
Monetary ones are used to reflect all objects in a single expression.

20:15.000 --> 20:26.000
In the Russian Federation, the unit of a monetary expression is rubles, and this is regulated by law.

20:27.000 --> 20:35.000
Natural ones can be divided into a group.

20:35.000 --> 20:46.000
Natural ones are used to reflect the same objects, but with different quantities.

20:46.000 --> 21:01.000
In order for all objects to be measurable, they must have a single expression.

21:01.000 --> 21:03.000
This is the monetary expression.

21:03.000 --> 21:12.000
The monetary expression of accounting objects ensures the reality of accounting indicators,

21:12.000 --> 21:18.000
their compatibility with the organization's economic activity.

21:18.000 --> 21:24.000
Now I want to give you a small example.

21:24.000 --> 21:28.000
Imagine a fruit store.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.000
What is in a fruit store?

21:31.000 --> 21:36.000
20,000 rubles in cash, 100 kilograms of oranges, and 20 kilograms of apples.

21:36.000 --> 21:40.000
Can you determine the total amount of goods in the store?

21:40.000 --> 21:44.000
Is this information I am giving you enough?

21:44.000 --> 21:47.000
No, you cannot.

21:47.000 --> 21:52.000
You cannot add up the cash register and the apples in the boxes.

21:52.000 --> 21:55.000
They are expressed in different units of measurement.

21:55.000 --> 22:00.000
To bring them to a single denominator, to calculate them,

22:00.000 --> 22:05.000
you need to add the information that oranges cost 50 rubles per kilogram,

22:05.000 --> 22:08.000
and apples cost 60 rubles per kilogram.

22:08.000 --> 22:14.000
You can add up the total amount of goods in the store, and you will see that it is 26,200 rubles.

22:14.000 --> 22:22.000
Thus, a single monetary expression makes the elements of accounting information comparable.

22:22.000 --> 22:31.000
Both the turnover of current bonds, the profits of assets, the sources of funds, and the creditor's debt.

22:32.000 --> 22:40.000
What is a balance? How will the real life of an enterprise be reflected in the balance?

22:40.000 --> 22:49.000
How do the assets of an organization, its assets, and the sources of its passive education reflect in the accounting balance?

22:49.000 --> 22:55.000
We will see this with you in the examples.

22:55.000 --> 23:03.000
Let's say that an industrial organization has a regular fund of 180,000 rubles.

23:03.000 --> 23:12.000
This fund provides the organization with all the necessary funds for its production activities.

23:12.000 --> 23:20.000
The main funds purchased for this money are 100,000 rubles.

23:20.000 --> 23:26.000
The organization purchased raw materials and materials from the regular capital fund for 25,000 rubles,

23:26.000 --> 23:32.000
purchased fuel for 5,000 rubles, and the bank had 50,000 rubles left.

23:32.000 --> 23:41.000
We will write down the assets in the balance on the left, and the passives on the right.

23:42.000 --> 23:50.000
The total amount of economic assets will be 180,000 rubles.

23:50.000 --> 23:57.000
The right side will have a passive fund that contains only one position of the regular capital fund,

23:57.000 --> 24:01.000
and this amount is also equal to 180,000 rubles.

24:01.000 --> 24:10.000
Our enterprise was created, and it started. How will the facts of economic life be reflected in the balance?

24:10.000 --> 24:18.000
Let's look at the examples. An enterprise acquires raw materials from a counteragent.

24:18.000 --> 24:28.000
What happens to the balance? What economic operations should an accountant carry out?

24:28.000 --> 24:31.000
How will this be reflected in the balance?

24:31.000 --> 24:36.000
The raw materials are acquired, which means that the raw materials reserves have been formed.

24:36.000 --> 24:43.000
The reserves are an active part of the balance. The asset is increasing.

24:43.000 --> 24:50.000
The raw materials are acquired, but the enterprise has not yet paid the money.

24:50.000 --> 24:54.000
This means that the debt to the counteragents appears.

24:54.000 --> 25:04.000
The debt is a passive part of the balance. The asset and the passive balance have increased.

25:04.000 --> 25:19.000
The debt to the counteragents is increased by transferring cash from the account of the organization of the raw materials recipient to the account of the counteragent.

25:19.000 --> 25:26.000
How will the accountant be able to reflect this in the balance?

25:26.000 --> 25:32.000
What economic operations should he carry out? What will the result be?

25:33.000 --> 25:42.000
If the debt is reduced, the amount of money transferred is reduced.

25:42.000 --> 25:56.000
The debt is reduced, the balance is passive, and the amount of money transferred is reduced.

25:57.000 --> 26:01.000
The money was paid to the counteragent from the account.

26:01.000 --> 26:05.000
The account is an active part of the balance.

26:05.000 --> 26:08.000
The balance is reduced and is in the asset.

26:08.000 --> 26:18.000
As a result of this economic operation, when the debt is reduced by transferring cash from the account of the organization of the counteragent,

26:18.000 --> 26:22.000
the balance is reduced, both the passive and the asset.

26:23.000 --> 26:32.000
The next economic operation is when the organization of the counteragent unloads the finished product from the warehouse.

26:32.000 --> 26:36.000
The balance of the finished product is reduced.

26:36.000 --> 26:39.000
The balance of the stock in the warehouse is reduced.

26:39.000 --> 26:43.000
The stock and the finished product are active parts of the balance.

26:43.000 --> 26:46.000
The asset is reduced.

26:46.000 --> 26:54.000
At the same time, the enterprise has not received a payment for the finished product.

26:54.000 --> 27:04.000
The article on the payment of the counteragent for the finished product is increasing.

27:04.000 --> 27:08.000
This is also an asset of the organization.

27:08.000 --> 27:10.000
This article is increasing.

27:10.000 --> 27:12.000
What happened to the asset?

27:12.000 --> 27:15.000
When the stock was reduced, the asset was reduced.

27:15.000 --> 27:21.000
When the debt was increased for the finished product, the asset was increased.

27:21.000 --> 27:33.000
The next economic operation is when the counteragent pays off its debt by transferring cash to the account of the organization of the supplier.

27:33.000 --> 27:35.000
For example, for the materials.

27:36.000 --> 27:42.000
The debt of the counteragent was in the asset.

27:42.000 --> 27:44.000
The asset is reduced.

27:44.000 --> 27:53.000
The money received by the counteragent is increased.

27:53.000 --> 27:56.000
The money is transferred to the bank's account.

27:56.000 --> 27:59.000
The asset is also increased.

28:00.000 --> 28:04.000
The last example.

28:04.000 --> 28:07.000
The organization receives a loan from the bank.

28:07.000 --> 28:18.000
The bank has transferred a loan amount to the account of the organization.

28:18.000 --> 28:22.000
How will this affect the balance?

28:22.000 --> 28:30.000
If the money is increased, and the money is an active part of the balance, the asset will increase.

28:30.000 --> 28:39.000
But the enterprise becomes a debtor of the bank for the amount of the loan.

28:39.000 --> 28:43.000
The debt to the bank is a passive part of the balance.

28:43.000 --> 28:46.000
The asset will increase.

28:46.000 --> 29:00.000
The main concept in accounting is that the balance asset must always be equal to its passive part.

29:00.000 --> 29:10.000
The main capital equation in accounting is that the asset is equal to the passive part.

29:10.000 --> 29:17.000
The passive part is the capital of the organization plus some obligations of the organization.

29:17.000 --> 29:20.000
This is the main capital equation in accounting.

29:20.000 --> 29:26.000
You should remember that the asset is equal to the capital plus obligations.

29:26.000 --> 29:34.000
This equation is used to determine the optimal structure of the organization's passives.

29:34.000 --> 29:47.000
We can say that the economic meaning of the balance is that the acquisition of the organization's assets must be provided by the availability of the relevant sources.

29:47.000 --> 29:53.000
But you know that nothing is taken from nothing, just like it doesn't disappear.

29:53.000 --> 30:00.000
If there is a source, there is money, the organization's assets or resources can be acquired,

30:00.000 --> 30:07.000
or the organization's materials, or money can be obtained at the organization's account.

30:07.000 --> 30:17.000
The organization's resources can be the funds of the founders and participants, the so-called statutory capital.

30:17.000 --> 30:24.000
The organization's creditors are obliged to use the assets as sources.

30:24.000 --> 30:31.000
The so-called stable passives are selected from the passives.

30:31.000 --> 30:36.000
This is the obligation that is legally postponed.

30:36.000 --> 30:43.000
For example, the debt to the amount of the salary of the organization's employees for the past month,

30:44.000 --> 30:51.000
the tax rate, the term of payment, which is also postponed compared to the end of the month.

30:51.000 --> 30:56.000
Maybe you know that the salary is always charged on the last day of the month,

30:56.000 --> 31:12.000
for example, in March, March 30, and the payment of the salary according to the collective agreement in the organization is expected on April 5, 8, 10.

31:12.000 --> 31:17.000
The same way taxes are charged on the last day of the month.

31:17.000 --> 31:27.000
Payment is provided by the Russian legislation, for example, a tax on the added value of the next month on the 20th,

31:27.000 --> 31:38.000
or a tax on the profit on the 28th, the next month of the accounting period.

31:39.000 --> 31:46.000
This is the group of obligations that are called stable passives.

31:46.000 --> 31:57.000
What we have seen, several economic operations and their impact on the balance, suggests several conclusions.

31:58.000 --> 32:09.000
The first conclusion is that any change in the capital and obligations of the organization should be accompanied by an increase or decrease in the share of its property.

32:09.000 --> 32:14.000
That is, the passive changes, the asset changes.

32:14.000 --> 32:22.000
The second conclusion is that when an operation is carried out, as a result of which the currency of the balance does not change,

32:22.000 --> 32:33.000
but only the structure of assets or passives changes, only the structure, that is, the size of passives and assets should not change either.

32:33.000 --> 32:41.000
In a normally operating organization, the size of the obligations of the organization usually corresponds to the amount

32:41.000 --> 32:52.000
that creditors can expect when liquidating an operating entity, with an expectation of meeting their requirements in full.

32:52.000 --> 33:01.000
The size of the capital in a normally operating organization corresponds to the value of the property of the organization,

33:01.000 --> 33:09.000
the value of the property subject to transfer to the founders and participants in the event of liquidation of the organization.

33:09.000 --> 33:22.000
It should be noted that the capital includes not only the statutory capital, the value of the property incurred when creating an organization,

33:22.000 --> 33:29.000
but also additional and reserve capital, as well as the amount of unallocated profit.

33:29.000 --> 33:37.000
If the result of the organization's activities in the previous accounting period was negative,

33:37.000 --> 33:46.000
then the amount of the loss received when determining the capital is taken into account with a minus sign,

33:46.000 --> 33:53.000
and in the forms of accounting, these amounts will be shown in round brackets.

33:53.000 --> 33:58.000
Now let's talk about the size of the organization's own capital.

33:58.000 --> 34:13.000
It should be noted that the organization's own capital can be determined based on the balance sheet of the accounting balance.

34:13.000 --> 34:26.000
It can be converted and obtained that the organization's capital is equal to the organization's assets minus its obligations.

34:26.000 --> 34:36.000
This equation is used to determine the value of the assets acquired at the expense of the organization's own funds,

34:36.000 --> 34:40.000
and it is called the organization's pure assets.

34:40.000 --> 34:50.000
If the organization does not have a reserve of the upcoming expenses, then the value of the pure assets is equal to the organization's capital.

34:50.000 --> 34:56.000
That is, our equation for pure assets is as follows.

34:56.000 --> 35:04.000
Pure assets are the organization's assets, reduced to the value of its obligations.

35:05.000 --> 35:13.000
Why do we need to count pure assets? Why do we need to know what they are equal to?

35:13.000 --> 35:20.000
When the size of the pure assets becomes smaller than the size of the declared statutory capital,

35:20.000 --> 35:26.000
the Russian legislation should either reduce its statutory capital,

35:26.000 --> 35:32.000
or change the organizational legal form, or be eliminated altogether.

35:33.000 --> 35:44.000
Let's see how the change in the organization's assets and passive balance is reflected in practice when performing typical economic operations.

35:44.000 --> 35:53.000
The life of an organization begins with its first entry balance.

35:53.000 --> 36:00.000
For example, let's take an organization whose entry balance looks like this.

36:00.000 --> 36:07.000
The main assets are 25,000 rubles, raw materials are 1,000 rubles,

