43:18.000 --> 43:27.000
The sum of these two sections is called the balance, or the result is called the balance currency.

43:27.000 --> 43:38.000
The first section includes articles such as non-returnable assets, basic funds, long-term financial investments, and unfinished construction.

43:38.000 --> 43:50.000
The second section, called returnable assets, includes articles such as reserves, debt, and money.

43:50.000 --> 43:59.000
The balance assets include three sections.

43:59.000 --> 44:04.000
Section number three is the balance assets, which include capital and reserves.

44:04.000 --> 44:11.000
There is share capital, and the additional capital that arises during the organization's activities.

44:11.000 --> 44:14.000
The reserves created form the reserve capital.

44:14.000 --> 44:22.000
The profits of previous years, the uncovered losses of previous years, the unallocated profits of the report year, and the uncovered losses of the report year.

44:22.000 --> 44:27.000
All these articles form the capital and reserves section.

44:27.000 --> 44:36.000
The passive section is separately considered for their expiry date.

44:36.000 --> 44:44.000
Long-term bonds, loans, and other passives form the fourth section of the balance.

44:44.000 --> 44:56.000
Short-term bonds, such as loans, credit debt, income of future periods, and reserves of future expenses form the fifth section of the balance.

44:56.000 --> 45:00.000
We call it the balance, or the balance of profits and losses.

45:00.000 --> 45:05.000
It seems like this is the only document that can be compiled.

45:05.000 --> 45:15.000
There are many types of balance. Let's try to understand their classification.

45:15.000 --> 45:20.000
