45:20.000 --> 45:26.000
The balance is distinguished by the date of creation.

45:26.000 --> 45:31.000
The passive balance, the current balance, the unallocated balance, and the liquidation balance.

45:31.000 --> 45:38.000
The passive balance is the first balance that the organization has in its life.

45:38.000 --> 45:42.000
You have already seen what the passive balance looks like.

45:42.000 --> 45:55.000
It is the capital and property that can be acquired for the organization's funds.

45:55.000 --> 46:09.000
Or the organization will be in debt to the funders.

46:09.000 --> 46:12.000
The first types of balance are the passive balance.

46:12.000 --> 46:22.000
The current balance is the balance that the enterprise has in its life.

46:22.000 --> 46:34.000
They can be initial, intermediate, quarterly, or monthly.

46:34.000 --> 46:39.000
And they can be the final balance at the end of the year.

46:39.000 --> 46:45.000
In addition to these two types, there are also liquidated balances.

46:45.000 --> 46:53.000
If the enterprise is on the verge of bankruptcy, but there is a chance to save it,

46:53.000 --> 47:03.000
