unfortunately, can be different.

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:15.000
Let's look at some cases of paradoxical accounting situations.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:20.000
For example, we have an organization.

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:25.000
It has a small balance.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:31.000
The organization has the main funds for some amount,

01:00:31.000 --> 01:00:35.000
let's say 2,000 rubles or 2,000 conditional units,

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:37.000
and the goods for 4,000 conditional units,

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:42.000
and the cash in the cash desk and the bank is also 2,000 units.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:45.000
The balance has 8,000 units in total.

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:50.000
The sources that the organization's funds were formed with

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:56.000
are the established capital of 5,500,

01:00:56.000 --> 01:01:02.000
the profit for the previous year of 1,500 conditional units,

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:08.000
and some credit debt that the organization has for 1,000 units.

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:14.000
The passive is also equal to the asset and is 8,000 conditional units.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:21.000
The organization, which has such a balance, is going to make a large purchase,

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:23.000
to buy a car.

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:29.000
Everything is purchased for money or for the promise to pay them in credit.

01:01:29.000 --> 01:01:34.000
The organization buys a car for 1,900 units.

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:40.000
In the table, you can see the movement of both cash and main funds

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:45.000
that were created in the organization's account, and the money was reduced.

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:50.000
What is paradoxical in this situation?

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:55.000
Pay attention to the fact that the money that was left on the organization's accounts,

01:01:55.000 --> 01:02:02.000
100 conditional units, is now not enough to pay off the debts.

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:06.000
The passive debt is 1,000 units.

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:16.000
The profit is there, but the organization is not able to pay off the debts.

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:18.000
The profit is there, but the money is not.

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.000
This is a paradoxical situation.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:23.000
The next situation.

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:32.000
The organization sells existing goods at a 10% discount.

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:36.000
The buyers have not received the money yet.

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:42.000
But the organization must show the profit it has already received.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:51.000
10% of 2,000 goods, 200 units of profit, must be recorded in the balance passive.

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:54.000
The profit has increased.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:56.000
Look at the article on cash.

01:02:56.000 --> 01:02:58.000
There is no more money.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:06.000
The profit is increasing, but the organization cannot pay off the debts.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:12.000
The organization continues to produce goods.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:17.000
But some of these goods are still in incomplete production.

01:03:17.000 --> 01:03:26.000
All stages of processing have not yet been completed.

01:03:27.000 --> 01:03:30.000
The finished goods are not formed.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:39.000
The incomplete production has appeared in the balance asset.

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:45.000
And in the balance passive, the profit has appeared.

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:47.000
You see the increase in profit.

01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:53.000
The profit has increased, but the money has not increased.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:56.000
This is not a rare situation.

01:03:56.000 --> 01:04:01.000
My director often asks me the same question.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:06.000
I see the profit, but can we pay off the dividends?

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:08.000
We still don't have the money.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:15.000
The money will appear as soon as they pay for the sold goods.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:18.000
The next paradoxical situation.

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:26.000
The organization has acquired the right to use software products for five years.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:30.000
50 conditional units have been paid for this right.

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:35.000
Since the organization will use these products for five years,

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:41.000
the expenses will be only one fifth of the total, 10 conditional units.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:49.000
40 units of the paid money will be used as a full asset for future periods.

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:53.000
A new line appears in the asset.

01:04:53.000 --> 01:05:02.000
The profits will decrease due to the fact that the organization has incurred costs

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:10.000
in the form of amortization of the right to use software products.

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:21.000
We have spent the money, but the result is not good.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:28.000
The company's ability to pay has been reduced, and this may lead to bankruptcy.

01:05:29.000 --> 01:05:32.000
The next situation.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:47.000
Real money payments are not made when the company's current expenses are compared to the expenses of future periods.

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:51.000
For example, the organization has acquired a license for several years,

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:58.000
and every year the cost of the license is partially transferred to expenses.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:03.000
The accountant creates a reserve of possible expenses,

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:09.000
increasing the expenses of the current period and showing the reserve in the passive account for the debitor's debt.

